<pad> A  man  has  appeared  in  court  charged  with  causing  the  death  of  a  woman  in  a  car  accident  in  Hampshire.  He  has  been  hospitalized  with  critical  injuries  and  has  been  granted  unconditional  bail.  The  trial  is  scheduled  for  December  3rd.
<pad> Activists  in  Edinburgh  staged  a  meeting  to  demand  action  on  the  refugee  crisis.

<pad> David  Rodriguez  Gomez,  known  as  "El  Gato,"  was  a  prominent  enforcer  for  Joaquin  "El  Chapo"  Guzman.  He  admitted  to  over  150  murders  and  claimed  participation  in  an  additional  2,000  killings.  Gomez  was  released  from  prison  on  Friday,  commencing  a  five-year  probationary  period.  Public  opinion  in  Mexico  is  polarized  regarding  his  premature  release.  Some  argue  that  he  has  yet  to  fully  atone  for  his  offenses,  while  others  contend  that  after  spending  over  twenty  years  behind  bars,  he  deserves  a  chance  to  reform.  Gomez  had  been  sentenced  for  his  role  in  the  assassination  of  gubernatorial  candidate  Enrique  Salazar  in  1994.  However,  he  later  cooperated  with  authorities  against  former  Security  Minister  Carlos  Arellano,  who  was  a  competitor  in  the  1994  state  elections  and  was  convicted  of  ordering  Salazar’s  murder.  Arellano  is  serving  a  28-year  sentence  and  was  once  a  key  ally  of  Guzman,  the  leader  of  the  Sinaloa  cartel,  which  battled  intensely  with  Mexican  government  forces.
<pad> Sharks'  player  wears  microphone  during  3-1  win,  but  equipment  is  turned  off  due  to  technical  difficulties.

<pad> An  elderly  male  is  under  investigation  for  financial  misconduct  at  a  care  facility  in  Whitby.  The  Regulatory  Board  for  Elderly  Homes  is  collaborating  with  law  enforcement  and  is  keeping  a  vigilant  watch  over  the  matter.

<pad> Eric  Jennings  testified  at  Child  Welfare  Commission  about  abuse  at  St.  Anne's  Shelter  in  Waterford  and  Orion  Children's  Center  in  Melbourne.  He  reported  sexual  exploitation  by  caregivers  and  elder  children.  Jennings  was  among  14  children  transferred  to  Australia  in  1955.  120  children  from  Ireland  were  relocated  to  Australia  as  part  of  migration  scheme.  Commission  is  investigating  child  maltreatment  in  Ireland  from  1922  to  1998.
